# Stage 1 Preparation

## Goal

Set up the hunt by defining what suspicious behavior needed to be investigated.

## Hunt Objective

The objective was to identify whether a virtual machine was accidentally exposed to the public internet and determine whether that exposure led to successful unauthorized access.

## Hypothesis

```text
If a virtual machine was exposed to the public internet, then external attackers may have attempted brute force logins. If account lockout controls were missing or weak, one of those attempts may have resulted in successful unauthorized access.
```

## Risk Factors

| Risk Factor | Why It Matters |
|---|---|
| Internet facing VM | Public exposure allows attackers and bots to discover the system |
| Remote login access | Exposed login services are common brute force targets |
| Weak credentials | Increases the chance of successful password guessing |
| No account lockout | Allows repeated login attempts without blocking the attacker |
| Shared services role | A compromised shared services system could impact important infrastructure |

