# Stage 2 Data Collection

## Goal

Gather relevant endpoint and authentication data to determine whether the device was exposed and whether suspicious login activity occurred.

## Data Collection Questions

| Question | Reason |
|---|---|
| Was the device exposed to the public internet? | Confirms whether the system had external attack surface |
| Did the device receive failed login attempts? | Identifies possible brute force activity |
| Which remote IPs were involved? | Helps identify suspicious sources |
| Did any suspicious IPs successfully log in? | Determines whether brute force attempts may have succeeded |
| Were successful logons expected or suspicious? | Helps separate normal activity from compromise |

## Data Sources Reviewed

| Table | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `DeviceInfo` | Confirm whether the device was internet facing |
| `DeviceLogonEvents` | Review failed and successful authentication events |

## Query: Confirm Internet Facing Status

```kql
DeviceInfo
| where DeviceName == "windows-target-"
| where IsInternetFacing == true
| order by Timestamp desc
```

## Finding

| Field | Value |
|---|---|
| Device | `windows-target-` |
| Internet Facing | `True` |
| Last Internet Facing Time | `2026-03-14T05:50:59.251508Z` |

## Interpretation

The device was confirmed to be internet facing. This validated the need to review authentication activity for brute force attempts and possible successful unauthorized access.

