# Stage 3 Data Analysis

## Goal

Analyze collected data to test the hypothesis and identify suspicious authentication patterns.

The primary focus was failed logon activity from remote IP addresses.

## Query: Identify Failed Remote Login Attempts

```kql
DeviceLogonEvents
| where LogonType has_any("Network", "Interactive", "RemoteInteractive", "Unlock")
| where ActionType == "LogonFailed"
| where isnotempty(RemoteIP)
| summarize Attempts = count() by ActionType, RemoteIP, DeviceName
| order by Attempts desc
```

## Finding

The exposed environment showed repeated failed login attempts from multiple remote IP addresses.

This behavior is consistent with brute force or password spraying activity.

## Top Failed Login Sources

| Remote IP | Failed Attempts | Assessment |
|---|---:|---|
| `20.113.160.179` | 473 | High volume failed login source |
| `38.225.206.208` | 346 | High volume failed login source |
| `185.156.73.169` | 319 | Repeated failed login source |
| `80.94.95.238` | 233 | Repeated failed login source |
| `83.222.191.62` | Reviewed | Included in suspicious IP validation set |

## Analysis Summary

The failed login activity showed that the internet facing system was being targeted by external sources.

Failed logons alone did not prove compromise. The next step was to determine whether any suspicious remote IP addresses successfully authenticated.

