# Stage 5 Response

## Goal

Mitigate confirmed risks and reduce the chance of future compromise.

## Response Actions Taken

| Response Action | Purpose |
|---|---|
| Hardened NSG rules | Restricted RDP traffic to specific approved endpoints |
| Removed broad public access | Reduced exposure to internet based attackers and bots |
| Implemented account lockout policy | Prevented unlimited password guessing attempts |
| Implemented MFA | Added an additional layer of authentication security |

## Recommended Security Controls

| Control | Reason |
|---|---|
| Disable public RDP access | RDP should not be directly exposed to the internet |
| Use VPN or Azure Bastion | Administrative access should require a secure access path |
| Allowlist trusted IPs | Limits who can attempt remote access |
| Enforce strong passwords | Reduces password guessing risk |
| Enable account lockout | Slows or blocks brute force attacks |
| Require MFA | Protects accounts even if passwords are guessed or stolen |
| Monitor internet facing devices | Helps detect accidental exposure quickly |
| Alert on failed logon spikes | Improves brute force detection |
| Review NSG rules regularly | Prevents accidental public exposure |

